commit.message: pre0.99.20-179: Use insert_byte instead of insert_char when decoding quoted-printable
pre0.99.20-179: The regular expression \&, which matches the whole match, was not being handled properly
pre0.99.20-178: s2 used instead of s1 in mark_window_attributes
pre0.99.20-177: Updated copyright year
pre0.99.20-176: Windows changes: Do not initialize the tty in batch mode; Install jed.rc
pre0.99.20-174,175: Windows specific changes: Load $JED_ROOT/etc/jed.conf if it exists; Distinguish Ctrl-H and BS keys
pre0.99.20-173: Instructions and scripts for building the editor using the MinGW compiler suite under windows.
pre0.99.20-172: Some documentation updates
pre0.99.20-171: Updated copyright year on source files
pre0.99.20-170: Added exec keyword to shmode.sl
pre0.99.20-169: Changed `unsigned int' to SLstring_Type, use of `const', etc for migration to slang-3
pre0.99.20-168: Replaced some combinations of flush/getkey with get_mini_response; updated docs
pre0.99.20-167: Removed configure failure message when libfontconfig is not found
pre0.99.20-166: Use the get_mini_response() function in the help functions that prompt for a key
pre0.99.20-165: Added an additional argument to jed_get_mini_response to suspend macro execution while the key is read
pre0.99.20-164: Avoid recursion into the input_pending function. This corrects a bug introduced by #163

pre0.99.20-163:  The xjed display was not always being updated after inserting a selection.  If the target for a selection
request is unknown, then use a default.  Additional xjed debugging messages were also added.
pre0.99.20-162: xjed: If the font name is prefixed with "xft:", then pass it to XftFontOpenName, otherwise use XftFontOpen
pre0.99.20-161: Turn off smart quoting of ~ characters

pre0.99.20-160: Defer the querying of the hostname from the OS until
     the get_hostname function has been called.  To avoid the query,
     add `get_hostname("localhost.local");' to your .jedrc file.
pre0.99.20-159: Changed the backquote key to run the quoted_insert command for jed-mode bindings.

pre0.99.20-158: Documentation updates:
- Optional argument to `what_char()' function (Morten Bo Johansen)
- References to space.mit.edu changed to jedsoft.org
pre0.99.20-157: Tweaked the c_insert_bra function to better detect the insertion of a '{' in a list context
pre0.99.20-156: Rebuilt libfuns.hlp
pre0.99.20-155: Removed obsolete orelse syntax from idl.sl
pre0.99.20-154: Added Debian desktop icons

pre0.99.20-153: Added debian-patches:
* INFO-DIR-SECTION and INFO-DIR-ENTRY added to the info files
* Updates to aclocal.m4, configure.ac
* Use UTF-8 encoding in iso2xxx.sl
* documentation fix for whatbuf() function
* spelling error in jed.1 and file.c
* Changed the default binding of the backquote key to self-insert
pre0.99.20-152: src/w32proc.c: A loop variable was getting incremented twice causing a leak on on win32 systems.
pre0.99.20-151: lib/ctags.sl: Previous changes to ctags.sl broke the processing of etags-formatted files.  The code was updated to correct this.
pre0.99.20-150: Call XftFontClose prior to exiting xjed to avoid a leak.
